    <!-- Main Content -->
    <main>
        <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
        <div class="header-meta">
            <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> March 21, 2026</p>
            <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> March 21, 2026</p>
            <p><strong>Version:</strong> 1.0</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Table of Contents -->
        <div class="toc">
            <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
            <ol>
                <li><a href="#1">What Are Cookies?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#2">Why We Use Cookies</a></li>
                <li><a href="#3">Types of Cookies We Use</a></li>
                <li><a href="#4">Third-Party Cookies & Services</a></li>
                <li><a href="#5">Cookie Consent & Management</a></li>
                <li><a href="#6">How to Delete or Disable Cookies</a></li>
                <li><a href="#7">Your Rights Under GDPR</a></li>
                <li><a href="#8">Changes to This Policy</a></li>
                <li><a href="#9">Contact Information</a></li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 1 -->
        <h2 id="1">1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
        <p>Cookies are small text files that are placed on your device (computer, tablet, or mobile phone) when you visit a website. They allow websites to recognize your device, remember your preferences, and enhance your browsing experience. Cookies are widely used across the internet and are considered standard practice in web technology.</p>
        <p>Each cookie typically contains:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>A unique identifier</li>
            <li>Expiration date (some expire when the browser closes, others persist for weeks or months)</li>
            <li>Domain information (which websites can access it)</li>
            <li>Data values specific to your interaction with that website</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Cookies do NOT contain malware, viruses, or executable code. They are purely informational text files used to improve your experience.</p>

        <!-- Section 2 -->
        <h2 id="2">2. Why We Use Cookies</h2>
        <p>AutoCognitix uses cookies to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Authenticate Users:</strong> Keep you logged in across sessions</li>
            <li><strong>Remember Preferences:</strong> Store your language choice, theme settings, and diagnostic history</li>
            <li><strong>Improve Performance:</strong> Analyze how users interact with our platform</li>
            <li><strong>Enhance Security:</strong> Detect and prevent fraudulent access attempts</li>
            <li><strong>Provide Analytics:</strong> Understand which features are most used and identify areas for improvement</li>
            <li><strong>Personalize Content:</strong> Deliver relevant diagnostic information based on your vehicle history</li>
            <li><strong>Measure Marketing Effectiveness:</strong> Track which advertising channels drive traffic to AutoCognitix</li>
        </ul>

        <!-- Section 3 -->
        <h2 id="3">3. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>

        <h3>3.1 Cookie Categories</h3>
        <p>AutoCognitix uses cookies in the following categories:</p>

        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Category</th>
                    <th>Purpose</th>
                    <th>Duration</th>
                    <th>Required?</th>
                    <th>Consent</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Necessary/Essential</strong></td>
                    <td>Authentication, security, platform functionality, CSRF protection</td>
                    <td>Session to 24 months</td>
                    <td>Yes</td>
                    <td>No consent needed (legally required for security)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Functional</strong></td>
                    <td>Remember user preferences, language settings, UI customization</td>
                    <td>Up to 12 months</td>
                    <td>No</td>
                    <td>User consent required (can be implied by continued use)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Analytics</strong></td>
                    <td>Google Analytics: page views, user behavior, traffic sources, device types</td>
                    <td>Up to 24 months</td>
                    <td>No</td>
                    <td>Explicit user consent required (ePrivacy Directive)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Marketing/Advertising</strong></td>
                    <td>Google Ads, Meta Pixel: track conversions, personalize ads, retargeting</td>
                    <td>Up to 24 months</td>
                    <td>No</td>
                    <td>Explicit user consent required (ePrivacy Directive)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Social Media</strong></td>
                    <td>LinkedIn, Facebook: enable social sharing, social login integration</td>
                    <td>Varies by platform</td>
                    <td>No</td>
                    <td>Explicit user consent required</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3>3.2 Essential Cookies</h3>
        <p>These cookies are <strong>required for the platform to function</strong> and cannot be disabled without breaking core features:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><code>session_id</code> - Maintains your authenticated session</li>
            <li><code>csrf_token</code> - Protects against Cross-Site Request Forgery attacks</li>
            <li><code>user_preferences</code> - Stores temporary UI state (sidebar collapsed, font size)</li>
            <li><code>locale</code> - Remembers your language preference (EN, HU)</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="important-box">
            <h3>Legal Basis for Essential Cookies</h3>
            <p>Essential cookies are set under Article 7(f) GDPR (Legitimate Interest) and ePrivacy Directive Article 5(3) exception. These cookies do not require your explicit consent because they are necessary for the security and functionality of our Service.</p>
        </div>

        <h3>3.3 Analytics Cookies</h3>
        <p>We use Google Analytics 4 to understand how users interact with AutoCognitix. This helps us identify:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Which diagnostic features are most frequently used</li>
            <li>Where users encounter difficulties in the interface</li>
            <li>Device and browser compatibility issues</li>
            <li>Geographic distribution of our user base</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Google Analytics cookies set by AutoCognitix:</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li><code>_ga</code> - Unique visitor identifier (expires 2 years)</li>
            <li><code>_gid</code> - Session identifier (expires 24 hours)</li>
            <li><code>_gat_gtag_UA_*</code> - Request throttling (expires 1 minute)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Google Analytics data is pseudonymized and your IP address is partially masked. You can opt out by installing the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank">Google Analytics Opt-Out Browser Extension</a>.</p>

        <h3>3.4 Marketing Cookies</h3>
        <p>We use advertising cookies to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Google Ads:</strong> Track conversion events (e.g., account signup) and retarget users who have visited AutoCognitix</li>
            <li><strong>Meta Pixel (Facebook):</strong> Track user actions for advertising and analytics purposes</li>
            <li><strong>Remarketing:</strong> Show relevant AutoCognitix ads to users on other websites they visit</li>
        </ul>
        <p>These cookies contain no personal identification data but allow advertisers to infer your interests based on browsing behavior.</p>

        <!-- Section 4 -->
        <h2 id="4">4. Third-Party Cookies & Services</h2>

        <h3>4.1 Third-Party Cookie Providers</h3>
        <p>AutoCognitix integrates with third-party services that may set their own cookies:</p>

        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Service</th>
                    <th>Purpose</th>
                    <th>Cookies Set</th>
                    <th>Privacy Policy</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Google Analytics</strong></td>
                    <td>User behavior analytics, traffic analysis</td>
                    <td>_ga, _gid, _gat_gtag_UA_*</td>
                    <td><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">google.com/privacy</a></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Google Ads</strong></td>
                    <td>Conversion tracking, remarketing, ad personalization</td>
                    <td>_gcl_au, frm, IDE</td>
                    <td><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">google.com/privacy</a></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Meta Pixel</strong></td>
                    <td>Conversion tracking, event monitoring, audience building</td>
                    <td>_fbp, _fbc</td>
                    <td><a href="https://www.facebook.com/policies/" target="_blank">facebook.com/policies</a></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>LinkedIn Insight</strong></td>
                    <td>B2B analytics, conversion tracking</td>
                    <td>li_gc, li_sugr, bcookie</td>
                    <td><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank">linkedin.com/legal</a></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Stripe Payment</strong></td>
                    <td>Payment processing, fraud prevention</td>
                    <td>Various payment tokens</td>
                    <td><a href="https://stripe.com/privacy" target="_blank">stripe.com/privacy</a></td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <div class="warning-box">
            <h3>Third-Party Data Sharing</h3>
            <p>By using AutoCognitix, you acknowledge that cookies may be set by these third parties. We are NOT responsible for third-party cookie practices, and we recommend reviewing their privacy policies directly for more information.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 5 -->
        <h2 id="5">5. Cookie Consent & Management</h2>

        <h3>5.1 Cookie Consent Banner</h3>
        <p>When you first visit AutoCognitix, a cookie consent banner appears asking you to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Accept All:</strong> Enable all cookies (Necessary + Functional + Analytics + Marketing)</li>
            <li><strong>Reject All:</strong> Disable all non-essential cookies</li>
            <li><strong>Manage Preferences:</strong> Choose which cookie categories to enable</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Your consent choice is stored in a cookie and applied across the AutoCognitix platform. You can change your preferences at any time.</p>

        <h3>5.2 Consent Requirements Under GDPR & ePrivacy Directive</h3>
        <p>Under EU regulations (GDPR Article 7, ePrivacy Directive Article 5(3)), we must obtain your <strong>explicit consent</strong> before setting non-essential cookies. Consent must be:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Freely given:</strong> Not a condition of using the Service</li>
            <li><strong>Informed:</strong> You must understand what cookies do before consenting</li>
            <li><strong>Specific:</strong> You consent to each cookie category separately</li>
            <li><strong>Unambiguous:</strong> An affirmative action (clicking "Accept" or selecting preferences)</li>
            <li><strong>Easy to withdraw:</strong> You can change your mind at any time</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="important-box">
            <h3>No Pre-Checked Consent</h3>
            <p>AutoCognitix does NOT use pre-checked boxes in the cookie consent banner. You must actively select which cookie categories you allow. Silence or inaction does NOT constitute consent.</p>
        </div>

        <h3>5.3 Managing Your Cookies</h3>
        <p>You can update your cookie preferences at any time by:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Clicking the cookie settings icon in the footer of any page</li>
            <li>Accessing Settings → Privacy → Cookie Preferences in your account</li>
            <li>Contacting support@autocognitix.hu</li>
        </ul>

        <!-- Section 6 -->
        <h2 id="6">6. How to Delete or Disable Cookies</h2>

        <h3>6.1 Browser Settings</h3>
        <p>You can disable cookies in your browser settings. Instructions for major browsers:</p>

        <h4>Google Chrome</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Click the menu icon (three dots) in the top-right corner</li>
            <li>Select Settings → Privacy and Security → Cookies and other site data</li>
            <li>Choose "Block all cookies" or manage exceptions for specific sites</li>
        </ol>

        <h4>Mozilla Firefox</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Click the menu icon (three horizontal lines) in the top-right corner</li>
            <li>Select Settings → Privacy & Security</li>
            <li>Under "Cookies and Site Data," select your preferred option (Allow, Limit to Current Session, or Block)</li>
        </ol>

        <h4>Apple Safari</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Click Safari in the menu bar</li>
            <li>Select Preferences → Privacy</li>
            <li>Under "Cookies and website data," select your preference</li>
        </ol>

        <h4>Microsoft Edge</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Click the menu icon (three dots) in the top-right corner</li>
            <li>Select Settings → Privacy, search, and services</li>
            <li>Under "Cookies and other site data," adjust your settings</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>6.2 Disabling Third-Party Cookies</h3>
        <p>Most browsers allow you to disable third-party cookies specifically while keeping essential cookies enabled:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Chrome:</strong> Settings → Privacy and Security → Third-party cookies → Select "Block third-party cookies"</li>
            <li><strong>Firefox:</strong> Settings → Privacy & Security → Enhanced Tracking Protection → Select "Strict"</li>
            <li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences → Privacy → Uncheck "Allow cross-site tracking"</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>6.3 Opt-Out Services</h3>
        <p>Some advertisers offer opt-out mechanisms:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank">Google Analytics Opt-Out Browser Extension</a></li>
            <li><strong>Meta (Facebook):</strong> <a href="https://www.facebook.com/ads/preferences/" target="_blank">Facebook Ads Preferences</a></li>
            <li><strong>Network Advertising Initiative:</strong> <a href="https://optout.networkadvertising.org/" target="_blank">NAI Consumer Opt-Out</a></li>
            <li><strong>Digital Advertising Alliance (DAA):</strong> <a href="https://optout.aboutads.info/" target="_blank">DAA Consumer Choice</a></li>
        </ul>

        <div class="important-box">
            <h3>Impact of Disabling Cookies</h3>
            <p>If you disable essential cookies, AutoCognitix may not function properly. You may lose:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Ability to log in to your account</li>
                <li>Saved diagnostic history</li>
                <li>Personalized recommendations</li>
                <li>Language and theme preferences</li>
            </ul>
            <p>We recommend allowing at least essential and functional cookies for the best experience.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 7 -->
        <h2 id="7">7. Your Rights Under GDPR</h2>

        <h3>7.1 Right to Access & Transparency</h3>
        <p>You have the right to know:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>What cookies are being set on your device</li>
            <li>Which organizations are setting them (first-party vs. third-party)</li>
            <li>How long they persist</li>
            <li>What data they contain</li>
            <li>How they are used to process your personal data</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>7.2 Right to Consent & Withdrawal</h3>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Give or withhold consent for non-essential cookies</li>
            <li>Change your mind and withdraw consent at any time</li>
            <li>Consent to some categories of cookies while rejecting others</li>
            <li>Not have your choices treated as a condition of using the Service</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>7.3 Right to Erasure (Deletion)</h3>
        <p>You can request that AutoCognitix delete cookies associated with your account. Contact privacy@autocognitix.hu with the request "Delete all cookies associated with my account [email]." We will comply within 30 days unless the cookie is necessary for security.</p>

        <h3>7.4 Right to Data Portability</h3>
        <p>You have the right to request a copy of all data processed through cookies, in a machine-readable format. Submit requests to privacy@autocognitix.hu.</p>

        <h3>7.5 Cookie Policy Complaints</h3>
        <p>If you believe AutoCognitix is not complying with GDPR or ePrivacy Directive regarding cookies, you may lodge a complaint with the National Authority for Data Protection and Freedom of Information (NAIH).</p>

        <!-- Section 8 -->
        <h2 id="8">8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>AutoCognitix may update this Cookie Policy at any time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Last Updated" date. If material changes are made to how we use cookies, we will notify you via email and request re-confirmation of your cookie preferences.</p>
        <p>Your continued use of AutoCognitix after any update constitutes your acceptance of the revised Cookie Policy.</p>

